text: Set on a private, north-facing lot in one of Southlakes most desirable pockets, 309 Woodsong Way offers a rare combination: a single-story custom home with architectural character, uncompromising quality, and a layout designed for modern living, all within walking distance to Southlake Town Square and zoned to coveted Carroll ISD. Warm hardwood floors, vaulted ceilings with stained wood beams, and arched architectural details create a timeless interior, while oversized windows bring in soft natural light and serene views of the backyard retreat. The heart of the home is a chefs kitchen anchored by a large granite island, outfitted with Wolf and Subzero appliances and elegant custom cabinetry with glass display fronts. Open to the living and breakfast areas, its a space equally suited for quiet mornings or gatherings that spill outside. And that transition outdoors? Custom bi-fold doors elegantly open the living area to a covered patio complete with a gas fireplace, built-in grill, beverage fridge, and Phantom screens for year-round enjoyment. Beyond, a Claffey-designed pool and spa with UV and ozone filtration glistens beneath a canopy of mature landscaping creating a private and peaceful experience. Inside, the primary suite is a retreat: spacious, light-filled, with a spa-style bath that includes a frameless glass shower, soaking tub, dual vanities, and a customized walk-in closet. Each of the three secondary bedrooms offers an en-suite bath, and one includes direct access to the patio. The home also features a elegant powder bath, dedicated game room, fully wired media room and a beautifully appointed office with beamed ceilings. Behind the scenes, every essential has been considered: whole-home generator, tornado shelter, air scrubbers, and a five-car garage setup with hydraulic lifts and epoxy floors. This is more than a home with premium finishes. Its a rare offering where comfort, privacy, and design converge in a location that speaks for itself.

text: Discover elegance and authenticity in this stunning custom home nestled in a distinguished Southlake community, perfect for both raising a family and entertaining. This home showcases European flair and robust construction, ensuring a blend of grandeur and security without the hassle of a Homeowners Association. Covering an impressive 6, 062 sq ft, this home features five bedrooms and five bathrooms. The master suite and guest bedroom are conveniently located on the first floor, while three more bedrooms await upstairs, providing ample space for your family. Each room is equipped with built in storage and accented with vintage Ralph Lauren wallpaper, custom crown molding, and trophy shelving ideal for celebratory displays. The chefs gourmet kitchen is a culinary dream, featuring top of the line Thermador appliances, two dishwashers, a commercial disposal, and a versatile range with both gas burners and griddle alongside four ovens. An oversized island and a sizable pantry complement the space beautifully, ensuring you have everything you need to host and entertain. The formal living room, office, and study area offer scenic views of the propertys lush landscape and luxury diving pool. Outdoor living is equally grand, with a pristine Pavestone entry, handmade gas lamps, and nearly half an acre to design your perfect outdoor haven or cabana. The homes prime location offers easy access to exceptional local schooling, with Old Union Elementary, Eubanks Intermediate School, and Dawson Middle School within walking distance. Enjoy a splendid array of nearby amenities, including generous parks and playgrounds, prestigious shopping at Southlake Town Square, and effortless commuting options to major destinations. Grant yourself the lifestyle you deserve in this serene and opulent Southlake home, where comfort meets quintessential luxury. Whether you're hosting lavish parties or enjoying quiet evenings by the pool, this home invites you to live remarkably.
